The following are major news items in leading Philippine
newspapers Friday: Manila Bulletin: -- Bill Gates, chairman and chief
executive officer of the world's biggest software giant the Microsoft
Corp., arrived Thursday night to strengthen the firm's presence here
and firm up its information technology-related partnerships with major
domestic conglomerates. The Business Daily: -- The Central Bank of the
Philippines said it would take a stronger hand in supervising and
monitoring the financial condition of the banking industry starting
from the third quarter this year. The Manila Times: -- The Bankers
Association of the Philippines (BAP) has decided to remove the peso
volatility band, BAP President Deogracias Vistan said Thursday.
